column1: The Eye of GNOME is the official image viewer for the GNOME desktop. It integrates with the GTK+ look and feel of GNOME, and supports many image formats for viewing single images or images in a collection.

column1: The Eye of GNOME also allows to view the images in a fullscreen slideshow mode or set an image as the desktop wallpaper. It reads the camera tags to automatically rotate your images in the correct portrait or landscape orientation.
column3: Eye of GNOME 也允許以全螢幕投影片模式檢視圖片或是將圖片設定為桌面的桌布。它會讀取數碼相機的標籤自動將你的影像旋轉到正確的直式或橫式方向。

column1: The web browser for GNOME, featuring tight integration with the desktop and a simple and intuitive user interface that allows you to focus on your web pages.
column3: GNOME 的網頁瀏覽器，帶來與桌面的緊密整合、簡易且直觀的使用者介面，讓你可以專注在你的網頁上。

column1: When files cannot be opened by the browser they are automatically downloaded to the download folder and opened with the appropriate application.

column1: Defines how the session will be restored during startup. Allowed values are 'always' (the previous state of the application is always restored), 'crashed' (the session is only restored if the application crashes) and 'never' (the homepage is always shown).
column3: 定義啟動時作業階段要如何還原。允許的數值有「always」(應用程式的前一個狀態永遠會還原)、「crashed」(作業階段只有在應用程式當機時還原) 和「never」(永遠只顯示首頁)。

column1: When this option is set to true, tabs will not start loading until the user switches to them, upon session restore.

column1: This option allows to set the process model used. Use 'shared-secondary-process' to use a single web process shared by all the tabs and 'one-secondary-process-per-web-view' to use a different web process for each tab.
column3: 這個選項允許設定使用的程序模型。使用「shared-secondary-process」讓所有分頁共享單一 web 程序，而「one-secondary-process-per-web-view」則會為每個分頁使用不同的 web 程序。

column3: 控制分頁列何時顯示。可能的數值有「always」(永遠顯示分頁列)、「more-than-one」(如果有兩個以上分頁才顯示分頁列) 和「never」(永遠不顯示分頁列)。

column1: Evolution is a personal information management application that provides integrated mail, calendaring and address book functionality.

column1: Evolution supports a wide range of industry standard data formats and network protocols for information exchange, with an emphasis on standards compliance and security. Evolution can also integrate smoothly with Microsoft Exchange by way of the \"Exchange Web Services\" (EWS) extension.
column3: Evolution 支援了用於資訊交換的廣範圍的工業標準資料格式與網絡協定，着重於標準的兼容性與安全性。Evolution 也可以與 Microsoft Exchange 透過「交換網頁服務」(EWS)延伸功能平順的整合。

column1: Some mailing lists set a Reply-To: header to trick users into sending replies to the list, even when they ask Evolution to make a private reply. Setting this option to TRUE will attempt to ignore such Reply-To: headers, so that Evolution will do as you ask it. If you use the private reply action, it will reply privately, while if you use the 'Reply to List' action it will do that. It works by comparing the Reply-To: header with a List-Post: header, if there is one.
column3: 有些通信論壇會設定 Reply-To: 標頭來誤導使用者傳送回覆的信件到論壇上，即使使用者已要求 Evolution 進行私人回覆也一樣。將這個選項設為 TRUE 會嘗試忽略 Reply-To: 標頭，因此 Evolution 就能根據你所要求的行動。如果你使用私人回覆動作，它就會進行回信給個人的動作；而如果你使用「回覆到論壇」動作，它也會照做。它的運作方式是比對 Reply-To: 標頭和 List-Post: 標頭，如果有的話。

column1: The contact list you are sending to is configured to hide list recipients.\n\nMany email systems add an Apparently-To header to messages that only have BCC recipients. This header, if added, will list all of your recipients in your message. To avoid this, you should add at least one To: or CC: recipient.

column1:
Hi.  Thanks for taking the time to download this preview release
of the Evolution groupware suite.

This version of Evolution is not yet complete. It is getting close,
but some features are either unfinished or do not work properly.

If you want a stable version of Evolution, we urge you to uninstall
this version, and install version %s instead.

If you find bugs, please report them to us at bugzilla.gnome.org.
This product comes with no warranty and is not intended for
individuals prone to violent fits of anger.

We hope that you enjoy the results of our hard work, and we
eagerly await your contributions!
column3:
你好。感謝你撥冗下載
Evolution 羣組套裝軟件搶鮮版。

此 Evolution 版本尚未完成。它即將告成，
但是部份功能未完成或者無法正常作業。

如果你需要可靠的 Evolution 版本，我們希望你取消安裝
此版本，然後安裝 %s 版本。

如果你發現設計問題，請到 bugzilla.ximian.com 通知我們。
此產品沒有任何保證而且不適用於
個人，以免引發任何不快。

我們希望你享受工作成果，而且我們
熱切希望你提供意見！

column1: S_elect the files you want to update:

Five or More is the GNOME port of a once-popular computer game. Align five or more objects of the same color into a line to cause them to disappear and score points. Earn many more points by lining up as many objects as possible before clearing them.
column3: 五子連色棋是把一度流行的遊戲移殖到 GNOME 的成果。將五個或更多同樣顏色的目標連成一線就能讓它們消失並獲得分數。在清除棋子之前只要連結愈多的棋子就能獲得愈多的分數。

column1: A family classic, the objective of Four-in-a-row is to build a line of four of your marbles while trying to stop your opponent (human or computer) from building a line of his or her own. A line can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal. The first player to connect four in a row is the winner!
column3: 傳統遊戲家族之一，四子連環棋的目的是將你的彈珠四個連成一直線，同時要阻止你的對手 (人類或電腦) 完成他(她)自己的連線。連線可以是水平、垂直或斜線。第一個將四個彈珠連成一直線的玩家就是勝利者！

column1: Four-in-a-row features multiple difficulty levels. If you're having trouble, you can always ask for a hint.
column3: 四子連環棋有多種難度等級。如果你遇到困難，可以隨時要求提示。

column1: Take a picture of the screen
gedit is the official text editor of the GNOME desktop environment. While aiming at simplicity and ease of use, gedit is a powerful general purpose text editor.
column3: gedit 是 GNOME 桌面環境的官方文字編輯器。着重於簡單、易用，gedit 是一個功能強大的多用途文字編輯器。

column1: Whether you are writing the next bestseller, programming an innovative application, or simply taking some quick notes, gedit will be a reliable tool to accomplish your task.
column3: 無論你是在撰寫下一本暢銷書、設計創新的應用程式，或者只是做個快速筆記，gedit 都會是能完成你工作的可靠工具。

column1: Its flexible plugin system allows you to tailor the application to your needs and adapt it to your workflow.
column3: 它多樣化的外掛程式系統允許你自選應用程式以符合你的需求與工作流程。

column1: Whether to use the system's default fixed width font for editing text instead of a font specific to gedit. If this option is turned off, then the font named in the \"Editor Font\" option will be used instead of the system font.
column3: gedit 是否使用系統預設的固定闊度字型作為編輯文字使用，而不用 gedit 指定的字型。如果關閉本選項，則會使用「編輯器字型」選項中的字型，而不用系統字型。

column1: A custom font that will be used for the editing area. This will only take effect if the \"Use Default Font\" option is turned off.
column3: 在編輯區域中使用的自選字型。本選項只有在關閉「使用預設字型」選項後才會生效。

column1: The ID of a GtkSourceView Style Scheme used to color the text.
column3: 用於文字顏色的 GtkSourceView 樣式架構 ID。

column1: Whether gedit should create backup copies for the files it saves.
column3: gedit 儲存檔案時是否建立備份複本。

column1: Whether gedit should automatically save modified files after a time interval. You can set the time interval with the \"Autosave Interval\" option.
column3: gedit 是否應每隔某段時間自動儲存修改過的檔案。你可以在「自動儲存相隔時間」選項中指定時間。

column1: Number of minutes after which gedit will automatically save modified files. This will only take effect if the \"Autosave\" option is turned on.
column3: gedit 會在幾分鐘後自動儲存修改過的檔案。本選項只有在「自動儲存」選項開啟後才會生效。

column1: Maximum number of actions that gedit will be able to undo or redo. Use \"-1\" for unlimited number of actions.
column3: gedit 中復原或取消復原次數的上限。設為“-1”則為無限次。

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines in the editing area. Use \"none\" for no wrapping, \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: 指定編輯區域如何換列。使用「none」代表不會換列，「word」代表在字詞間換列，及「char」代表在個別字符間換列。請注意，設定值是會分辨大小寫的，所以請確保設定值和上面所列出的完全一致。

column1: Last split mode choice for line wrapping mode
column3: 用於換列模式的上次分隔模式選項

column1: Specifies the last split mode used with line wrapping mode, so that when wrapping mode is off we still remember the split mode choice. Use \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries.
column3: 指定上次用於換列模式的分隔模式，如此當換列模式關閉時我們仍能記住分隔模式選項。使用「word」表示以單字為換列根據據，而「char」表示以每個字符為換列根據據。

column1: Specifies the number of spaces that should be displayed instead of Tab characters.
column3: 指定顯示 Tab 字符時會以多少個空格代替。

column1: Whether gedit should insert spaces instead of tabs.
column3: gedit 應否使用空格來代替 Tab 字符。

column1: Whether gedit should enable automatic indentation.
column3: gedit 是否應啟用自動縮排的功能。

column1: Whether gedit should display line numbers in the editing area.
column3: gedit 應否在編輯區域中顯示列號。

column1: Whether gedit should highlight the current line.
column3: gedit 應否在當前的行上啟用色彩顯示功能。
高亮度顯示成對的括號

column1: Whether gedit should highlight matching brackets.
column3: gedit 是否應以色彩顯示與目前選取的成對的弧號。

column1: Whether gedit should display the right margin in the editing area.
column3: gedit 應否在編輯區域中顯示右邊邊界。

column1: Specifies the position of the right margin.

Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use \"disabled\" to always move at the start/end of the line, \"after\" to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, \"before\" to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and \"always\" to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line.
column3: 指定按下 HOME 與 END 鍵時游標要如何移動。使用「disabled」(停用)游標會移至行的開始/結束處。使用「after」(之後)游標會在第一次按下按鍵時移至行的開始/結束處，第二次按下按鍵時移至行的開始/結束處且略過空白字符。使用「before」(之前)游標會在移至行的開始/結束前先移到文字的開始/結束處。使用「always」(永遠)游標會以移至文字的開始/結束處代替移至行的開始/結束處。

column1: Whether gedit should restore the previous cursor position when a file is loaded.
column3: gedit 載入檔案後應否回到先前的游標位置。

column1: Whether gedit should enable syntax highlighting.
column3: gedit 應否啟用語法色彩顯示的功能。

column1: Whether gedit should highlight all the occurrences of the searched text.
column3: gedit 應否在搜尋後替匹配的字串加上標示。
確保結尾以 Newline 結束

column1: Whether gedit will ensure that documents always end with a trailing newline.
column3: gedit 應否確保文件結尾是以換行(newline)結束。

column1: Whether the toolbar should be visible in editing windows.
column3: 編輯視窗應否顯示工具列。

column1: Specifies when to show the notebook tabs. Use \"never\" to never show the tabs, \"always\" to always show the tabs, and \"auto\" to show the tabs only when there is more than one tab. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: 指定打印時如何換列。使用“GTK_WRAP_NONE”代表不會換列，“GTK_WRAP_WORD”代表在字詞間換列，及“GTK_WRAP_CHAR”代表在個別字符間換列。請注意，設定值是會分辨大小寫的，所以請確保設定值和上面所列出的完全一致。

column1: Whether the status bar at the bottom of editing windows should be visible.
column3: 編輯視窗的底部應否顯示狀態列。

column1: Whether the side panel at the left of editing windows should be visible.
column3: 編輯視窗左側是否應顯示側邊面板。
最近開啟檔案數目的上限

column1: Specifies the maximum number of recently opened files that will be displayed in the \"Recent Files\" submenu.
column3: 指定在「最近的檔案」副選單中，可以顯示多少個最近開啟的檔案。

column1: Whether gedit should print syntax highlighting when printing documents.
column3: gedit 應否在打印文件時加上語法色彩處理。

column1: Whether gedit should include a document header when printing documents.
column3: gedit 應否在打印文件時加上頁首。

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines for printing. Use \"none\" for no wrapping, \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: 指定列印時如何換列。使用「none」代表不會換列，「word」代表在字詞間換列，及「char」代表在個別字符間換列。請注意，設定值是會分辨大小寫的，所以請確保設定值和上面所列出的完全一致。

column1: If this value is 0, then no line numbers will be inserted when printing a document. Otherwise, gedit will print line numbers every such number of lines.
column3: 如果數值是 0，當打印文件時不會打印列號。否則，gedit 會每隔指定的列數打印列號。
打印時使用的內文字型

column1: Specifies the font to use for a document's body when printing documents.
column3: 指定打印文件時文件內容所用的字型。
打印時使用的頁首字型

column1: Specifies the font to use for page headers when printing a document. This will only take effect if the \"Print Header\" option is turned on.
column3: 指定打印文件時頁首所用的字型。本選項只有在「打印頁首」選項的值開啟的時候生效。
打印列號時使用的字型

column1: Specifies the font to use for line numbers when printing. This will only take effect if the \"Print Line Numbers\" option is non-zero.
column3: 指定打印時列號所用的字型。本選項只有在「打印列號」選項的值不是零的時候生效。

column1: Sorted list of encodings used by gedit for automatically detecting the encoding of a file. \"CURRENT\" represents the current locale encoding. Only recognized encodings are used.
column3: 這裏是一系列已排序的編碼，gedit 會根據這個清單自動偵測檔案的字符編碼。「CURRENT」表示使用目前地區設定的編碼。只會使用能識別的編碼。

column1: List of encodings shown in the Character Encoding menu in open/save file selector. Only recognized encodings are used.
column3: 在開啟/儲存檔案對話方塊中的「字符編碼」選單，會顯示這裏列出的編碼。只會使用能辨識的編碼。

column1: List of active plugins. It contains the \"Location\" of the active plugins. See the .gedit-plugin file for obtaining the \"Location\" of a given plugin.

column1: Glade is a RAD tool to enable quick & easy development of user interfaces for the GTK+ 3 toolkit and the GNOME desktop environment.
column3: Glade 是能快速 & 簡單開發 GTK+ 3 工具箱的使用者介面和 GNOME 桌面環境的 RAD 工具。

column1: The user interfaces designed in Glade are saved as XML and these can be loaded by applications dynamically as needed by using GtkBuilder or used directly to define a new GtkWidget derived object class using GTK+ new template feature.
column3: Glade 中設計的使用者介面是以 XML 儲存，並且能根據需求使用 GtkBuilder 在應用程式中動態載入，或是使用 Gtk+ 新的範本功能在 GtkWidget 衍生的物件類別中直接使用。

column1: By using GtkBuilder, Glade XML files can be used in numerous programming languages including C, C++, C#, Vala, Java, Perl, Python, and others.
column3: 使用 GtkBuilder，Glade XML 檔案可以用於許多種程式語言，包含 C、C++、C#、Vala、Java、Perl、Python 等等。

The sole purpose of this survey is to better know our user base.
Your email address will be used to uniquely identify you as a Glade user and send you back a modification token in case you want to modify something or add extra comments.
Only statistics compiled from the whole dataset will be shared publicly.
Individual data will be stored in a private database and it will not be shared with the public or any other third party.
column3:
本問卷的唯一目的是為了更了解我們的使用者羣。
 你的電子郵件地址將被用來做為 Glade 使用者的唯一識別以及當你想修改的東西或者加上額外註解時送回修改記號給你之用。
只有從整個資料庫編譯後的統計資料才會公開共享。
個人資料將被存儲在一個專用資料庫，它不會被公開或與任何其他第三者分享。

A simple GNOME 3 application to access remote or virtual systems. Unlike some other virtual machine management software, Boxes is targeted towards typical desktop end-users. For this reason, Boxes will not provide many advanced options to tweak virtual machines. Instead Boxes will focus on getting things working out of the box with very little input from user.
column3: 簡單的 GNOME 3 應用程式，能存取遠端或虛擬系統。不同於其他的虛擬機器管理軟件，Boxes 的目標對象為典型的桌面終端使用者。基於這個理由，Boxes 不會提供許多校調虛擬機器的進階選項。取而代之的，Boxes 會着重在讓使用者不需多做輸入就可以讓事情得以運作。

column1: You want to install Boxes if you just want a very safe and easy way to try out new operating systems or new (potentially unstable) versions of your favorite operating system(s), or need to connect to a remote machine (for example, in your office).
column3: 如果你只是想要一個非常安全、簡單的方式來嘗試新的作業系統或你喜好的作業系統的新版本 (通常是不穩定版本)，或是需要連線到遠端機器 (例如，你的辦公室電腦)，你會需要 Boxes。

column1: Calculates the number of compounding periods necessary to increase an investment of present value to a future value, at a fixed interest rate per compounding period.
column3: 計算一項投資的現值要到達某未來值所需的複利期數，每個複利期間的利率為固定的。

column1: Calculates the depreciation allowance on an asset for a specified period of time, using the double-declining balance method.
column3: 計算在指定的期間中某資產的折舊免稅額，使用雙倍餘額遞減法。

column1: Calculates the future value of an investment based on a series of equal payments at a periodic interest rate over the number of payment periods in the term.
column3: 計算投資的未來值，根據一系列等額付款，按照約定付款期數的定期利率。

column1: Calculates the resale price of a product, based on the product cost and the wanted gross profit margin.
column3: 計算轉售價格的產品，根據產品成本和希望的毛利率。

column1: Calculates the amount of the periodic payment of a loan, where payments are made at the end of each payment period.
column3: 計算出定期支付的貸款數額，支付款項的時刻為每個付款期間結束時。

column1: Calculates the present value of an investment based on a series of equal payments discounted at a periodic interest rate over the number of payment periods in the term.
column3: 計算投資的現值，根據一系列等額付款，按照約定付款期數的定期利率下進行折現。

column1: Calculates the periodic interest necessary to increase an investment to a future value, over the number of compounding periods.
column3: 計算投資增加到未來值所需的定期利率，按照複利期數。

column1: Calculates the straight-line depreciation of an asset for one period. The straight-line method of depreciation divides the depreciable cost evenly over the useful life of an asset. The useful life is the number of periods, typically years, over which an asset is depreciated.
column3: 計算一期間內資產的直線折舊。直線折舊法在資產可用年限內將折舊花費平均分攤。可用年限指資產折舊的期數，典型狀況下為年。

column1: Calculates the depreciation allowance on an asset for a specified period of time, using the Sum-of-the-Years'-Digits method. This method of depreciation accelerates the rate of depreciation, so that more depreciation expense occurs in earlier periods than in later ones. The useful life is the number of periods, typically years, over which an asset is depreciated.
column3: 計算在指定的期間中某資產的折舊免稅額，使用年數總和法。這個折舊方式會加速折舊率，所以前期會比後期有更多折舊費用。可用年限是指該資產折舊的週期數 (通常為年)。

column1: Calculates the number of payment periods that are necessary during the term of an ordinary annuity, to accumulate a future value, at a periodic interest rate.
column3: 計算普通年金累積至未來值所需的付款期數，按照某一定期利率。

column1: Perform arithmetic, scientific or financial calculations
column3: 進行數字、科學或金融的計算

column1: GNOME Calculator is an application that solves mathematical equations. Though it at first appears to be a simple calculator with only basic arithmetic operations, you can switch into Advanced, Financial, or Programming mode to find a surprising set of capabilities.
column3: GNOME 計數機是用來解決數學等式的應用程式。它一開始只顯示具備基礎數學運算功能的簡單計數機，你可以切換為進階、金融或程式設計模式以符合你的需求。

column1: The Advanced calculator supports many operations, including: logarithms, factorials, trigonometric and hyperbolic functions, modulus division, complex numbers, random number generation, prime factorization and unit conversions.
column3: 進階計數機支援許多運算方式，包含：對數、階乘、三角函數和雙曲函數、模數除法、複數、產生數數、分解質因數和單位轉換。

column1: Financial mode supports several computations, including periodic interest rate, present and future value, double declining and straight line depreciation, and many others.
column3: 金融模式支援多種運算，包含定期利率、現在和未來值、雙倍餘額遞減和直線折舊，以及其他許多方式。

column1: Programming mode supports conversion between common bases (binary, octal, decimal, and hexadecimal), boolean algebra, one’s and two’s complementation, character to character code conversion, and more.
column3: 程式設計模式支援許多常用基礎的換算 (二進位、八進位、十進位和十六進位)，邏輯代數，一與二的補數、字符對字符代碼轉換等等。

column1: GNOME Color Profile Viewer shows installed color profiles on your system and allows you to calibrate displays, printers and cameras using a wizard.
column3: GNOME 色彩描述檔檢視器可顯示你系統上安裝的色彩描述檔，並讓你使用精靈校準顯示器、打印機、攝影機。

column1: This functionality is typically used by GNOME Control Center from the color panel although can be used on its own.
column3: 此功能通常經由 GNOME 控制中心的顏色面板使用，但也可自行使用。

column1: Inspect and compare installed color profiles
column3: 檢查並比較已安裝的色彩描述檔

column1: Add a profile for the device
column3: 加入這個裝置的描述檔

column1: Remove a profile from the device
column3: 移除這個裝置的描述檔

column1: A CIE 1931 diagram shows a 2D representation of the profile gamut
column3: CIE 1931 圖表顯示的是描述檔色域的 2D 呈現樣貌

column1: A tone reproduction curve is the mapping of scene luminance to display luminance
column3: 色調再製曲線顯示的是場景輝度與顯示器輝度之間的映射關係

column1: A video card gamma table shows the curves loaded into the display
column3: 顯示卡 Gamma 表顯示的是該顯示器載入的曲線

column1: This shows what an image would look like if saved with the profile
column3: 這顯示的是若以該描述檔儲存影像時看來會是什麼樣貌

column1: This shows what an image would look like if opened with the profile
column3: 這顯示的是若以該描述檔開啟影像時看來會是什麼樣貌

column1: Named colors are specific colors that are defined in the profile
column3: 命名的色彩是描述檔中定義過的特定色彩

column1: Metadata is additional information stored in the profile for programs to use.
column3: 中介資料是儲存於描述檔中供程式使用的額外資訊。

column1: This pre-calibrates the screen by sending colored and gray patches to your screen and measuring them with the hardware device.
column3: 這樣會預先校準螢幕，它會傳送有顏色與灰階的色塊到螢幕上並以硬件裝置測量它們。

column1: Reading the patches using the color measuring instrument.
column3: 正在使用顏色測量儀器讀取色塊。

column1: Drawing the generated patches to the screen, which will then be measured by the hardware device.
column3: 在螢幕上繪出產生的色塊，好用來讓硬件裝置測量。

column1: Generating the ICC color profile that can be used with this screen.
column3: 正在產生用於這個螢幕的 ICC 色彩描述檔。

column1: Copying source image, chart data and CIE reference values.
column3: 正在複製來源圖片、圖表資料和 CIE 參考數值。

column1: Detecting the reference patches and measuring them.
column3: 正在偵測參考色塊並測量它們。

column1: Generating the ICC color profile that can be used with this device.
column3: 產生這個裝置可適用的 ICC 色彩描述檔。

column1: Rendering the patches for the selected paper and ink.
column3: 正在以選取的紙張和墨水繪製色塊。

column1: Wait for the ink to dry
Please wait a few minutes for the ink to dry. Profiling damp ink will produce a poor profile and may damage your color measuring instrument.
column3: 請等候幾分鐘讓墨水乾掉。使用未乾的墨水會產生不良的描述檔並且可能損壞你的顏色測量儀器。

column1: Setting up the instrument for use…
column3: 正在設定要使用的儀器…

column1: The sample could not be read at this time.
column3: 在這個時候無法讀取樣本。

column1: No firmware is installed for this instrument.
column3: 尚未安裝這個儀器的韌體。

column1: The pattern match wasn't good enough. Ensure you have the correct type of target selected.
column3: 圖案的比對不夠好。請確定你選擇了正確的目標類型。

column1: The measuring instrument got no valid readings. Please ensure the aperture is fully open.
column3: 測量儀器沒有得到有效的讀取值。請確定光圈是完全打開的。

column1: The measuring instrument is busy and is not starting up. Please remove the USB plug and re-insert before trying to use this device.
column3: 這個測量儀器正在忙碌中並且尚未啟動。在使用這個裝置前請將 USB 接頭拔出後重新插入。

column1: Failed to read the strip correctly.
Failed to read the color sample correctly.
column3: 無法正確的讀取色彩樣本。

column1: It looks like you've measured the wrong strip.
column3: 你似乎測量了錯誤的長條。

column1: If you've really measured the right one, it's okay, it could just be unusual paper.
column3: 如果你真的測量了正確的長條，那也沒關係，可能是這張紙太特殊了。

column1: The device could not measure the color spot correctly.
column3: 裝置無法正確的測量顏色點。

column1: Place the colorimeter on the area of white next to the letter and click and hold the measure switch.
column3: 將色度計放在文字旁的白色區域，點選並按住測量開關。

column1: Slowly scan the target line from left to right and release the switch when you get to the end of the page.
column3: 從左到右緩慢的掃描目標行，當你到達紙張結尾時放開開關。

column1: Ensure the center of the device is properly aligned with the row you are trying to measure.
column3: 請確定裝置的中央正對着你嘗試測量的列。

column1: If you make a mistake, just release the switch, and you'll get a chance to try again.
column3: 如果出錯，只要你放開開關，就有機會再試一次。

column1: Preparing the data for the printer.
column3: 正在準備打印機的資料。

column1: Sending the targets to the printer.
column3: 正在傳送目標至打印機。

column1: Please attach the measuring instrument to the center of the screen on the gray square like the image below.
column3: 請將測量儀器如下圖一樣放在螢幕中央的灰色方塊上。

column1: Please attach the measuring instrument to the center of the screen on the gray square.
column3: 請將測量儀器放在螢幕中央的灰色方塊上。

column3: 請將測量儀器如下圖一樣設定為螢幕模式。

column1: Please set the measuring instrument to screen mode.
column3: 請將測量儀器設定為螢幕模式。

column1: Please set the measuring instrument to calibration mode like the image below.
column3: 請將測量儀器如下圖一樣設定為校準模式。

column3: 請將測量儀器設定為校準模式。

column1: Are you sure you want to cancel the calibration?
column3: 你確定要取消校準作業嗎？

column1: Any existing screen correction will be temporarily turned off and the brightness set to maximum.
column3: 任何既有的螢幕校正會暫時關閉，此外亮度會設定為最大值。

column1: You can cancel this process at any stage by pressing the cancel button.
column3: 你可以在任何階段按下取消按按鈕來取消此程序。

column1: Click here to show the profile

column1: The camera has been calibrated successfully.

To view details about the new profile or to undo the calibration visit the control center.
column3: 若要檢視有關新描述檔的詳細資料，或是取消校準，請造訪 控制中心。

column1: You can use the profile with Linux, Apple OS X and Microsoft Windows systems.
column3: 你可以在 Linux、Apple OS X 與 Microsoft Windows 系統上使用色彩描述檔。

column1: Before calibrating the display, it is recommended to configure your display with the following settings to get optimal results.
column3: 在校準顯示器之前，建議根據下列設定值來設定你的顯示器以取得最佳結果。

column1: You may want to consult the owner's manual for your display on how to achieve these settings.
column3: 你可能需要參考顯示器的使用手冊以了解如何完成這些設定值。

column1: Reset your display to the factory defaults.
column3: 將顯示器重設為出廠預設值。

column1: Disable dynamic contrast if your display has this feature.
column3: 如果你的顯示器有動態對比功能請停用它。

column1: Configure your display with custom color settings and ensure the RGB channels are set to the same values.
column3: 將你的顯示器以自選的顏色設定值來設定，並確定 RGB 頻道都設定為同一數值。

column1: If custom color is not available then use a 6500K color temperature.
column3: 如果無法使用自選顏色，那就使用 6500K 色溫。

column1: Adjust the display brightness to a comfortable level for prolonged viewing.
column3: 調整顯示器亮度至舒適的等級以利長時間觀看。

column1: For best results, the display should have been powered for at least 15 minutes before starting the calibration.
column3: 為了最佳的結果，在開始校準之前顯示器應該開啟至少 15 分鐘。

column1: Calibration and profiling software is not installed.
column3: 尚未安裝校準與分析軟件。

column1: These tools are required to build color profiles for devices.
column3: 這些工具是建立裝置的色彩描述檔時必要的。

column1: Common color target files are not installed on this computer.
column3: 通用顏色目標檔案沒有安裝在這臺電腦上。

column1: Color target files are needed to convert the image to a color profile.
column3: 需要顏色目標檔案才能將圖片轉換為色彩描述檔。

column1: Do you want them to be installed?
If you already have the correct file, you can skip this step.
column3: 如果你已經有正確的檔案，可以略過這個步驟。

column1: Before profiling the device, you have to manually capture an image of a calibration target and save it as a TIFF image file.
column3: 在分析這個裝置前，你必須手動擷取一張校準目標的圖片並將它儲存為 TIFF 圖片檔。

column1: Ensure that the contrast and brightness are not changed and color correction profiles have not been applied.
column3: 請確定對比和亮度都沒有改變，而且尚未套用顏色校正描述檔。

column1: The device sensor should have been cleaned prior to scanning and the output file resolution should be at least 200dpi.
column3: 裝置的感測器應該在掃描前先完成清潔，而輸出檔案的解像度應該至少有 200dpi。

column1: Ensure that the white-balance has not been modified by the camera and that the lens is clean.
column3: 請確定白平衡沒有被攝影機修改過，而且鏡頭也是乾淨的。

column1: Please select the calibration target type.
What target type do you have?
Select the monitor type that is attached to your computer.
column3: 選取連接至你電腦的螢幕類型。

column1: Benchmarking involves measuring the transfer rate on various area of the device as well as measuring how long it takes to seek from one random area to another. Please back up important data before using the write benchmark.
column3: Benchmarking 包含測量裝置在各個區域的傳輸率以及從一個亂數區域尋找另一個亂數區要花多久時間。在使用寫入評測之前請先備份重要的資料。

column1: Benchmarking the write-rate of a disk requires exclusive access to the disk (e.g. the disk or its partitions cannot be mounted or in use) and involves reading data and then writing it back. As a result, the contents of the disk is not changed.\n\nIf not checked, the write-part of the benchmark will not be done but on the other hand exclusive access to the device is not needed (e.g. the disk or device can be in use).
column3: 評測磁碟的寫入速率需要對磁碟有全部的存取權 (例如，這個磁碟或其中的分割區不能被掛載或在使用中)，並且會讀取資料後再將它寫回去。所以，磁碟機的內容並不會被更改。\n\n如果不核取此項，寫入部分的評測就不會執行，另一方面來說也就不需要對磁碟有全部的存取權 (例如，磁碟機或裝置可以在使用中)。

column1: Number of samples. Bigger number produces a more accurate picture of access time patterns but takes more time.
column3: 取樣的數目。較大的數目會產生較準確的存取時間模式概觀，但是會花上較多的時間。

column1: The number of MiB (1048576 bytes) to read/write for each sample. Big sample sizes tend to produce more accurate benchmarks at the cost of the benchmark taking more time.
column3: 每個樣本要讀取/寫入的 MiB 數 (1048576 位元組)。大型樣本會產生較準確的評測結果，但同時會花費較多的時間。

column1: Number of samples. Bigger number produces more smooth graphs but the benchmark will take more time.
column3: 取樣的數目。較大的數目會產生較平滑的圖表，但是評測會花上較多的時間。

column1: GNOME Klotski is a set of block sliding puzzles. The objective is to move the patterned block to the area bordered by green markers. To do so, you'll need to slide other blocks out of the way. Complete each puzzle in as few moves as possible!
column3: GNOME 華容道是一組方塊滑動謎題。目標是將有圖案的方塊移動到有綠色標記圍位的區域。要做到這點，你需要將路徑上其他的方塊移走。儘可能以最少步數完成每個謎題！

column1: GNOME Klotski comes with nearly thirty different puzzle layouts of varying difficulty. Some of the layouts are similar and only the size of one or more blocks differ. Other layouts have more variety.
column3: GNOME 華容道內含近三十種不同難度的謎題配置。其中部分配置是類似的，差別只有一或多個方塊不同。其他配置會有更多的變化。

column1: A solitaire version of the classic Eastern tile game. Tiles are stacked on the board at the start of the game. The goal is to remove all the tiles in as little time as possible. Select two matching tiles and they will disappear from the board, but you can only select a tile if there is an empty space to its left or right at the same level. Be careful: tiles that look alike may actually be slightly different.
column3: 傳統東方麻雀遊戲的啤牌版本。遊戲開始時麻雀牌都堆疊在棋盤上。目標是儘可能在最短時間內移除所有的麻雀牌。選擇兩個相同的麻雀牌，它們就會從棋盤上消失，但你只能選擇在同一層中左右有空位的麻雀牌。注意：看起來很像的麻雀牌可能實際上還是會有一點差別。

column1: GNOME Mahjongg features a variety of starting layouts, some easy and some difficult. If you get stuck, you can ask for a hint, but this adds a large time penalty.
column3: GNOME 上海麻雀有多種起始的配置，有些簡單有些困難。如果你遇到難題，可以要求提示，但這樣會加上大量的時間。

column3: 把相同牌面的麻雀一對對地移走

column1: GNOME Mines is a puzzle game where you search for hidden mines. Flag the spaces with mines as quickly as possible to make the board a safer place. You win the game when you've flagged every mine on the board. Be careful not to trigger one, or the game is over!
column3: GNOME 拆地雷 (Mines) 是一種讓你搜尋隱藏地雷的謎題。儘快將遊戲盤中的地雷標上旗標讓遊戲盤變成安全的地方。當你標上遊戲盤中每一個地雷時就贏得遊戲。請小心不要觸發任何一個，否則遊戲就會結束！

column1: Guide a worm around a maze
column3: 引導不斷移動的小蟲蟲避開畫面的障礙物

column1: Control a worm in its quest to eat bonuses and become longer. Outmaneuver enemy worms while eating doughnuts and ice cream to increase your length. Each worm has ten lives and loses one by running into a wall, another worm, or itself. The enemy worms are after the same bonuses that you are, so be careful: if they become too large, you won't have much room for movement.
column3: 控制蟲蟲讓牠吃下獎賞並且變得愈來愈長。用智慧避開敵人，同時吃下甜甜圈和雪糕來增加你的長度。每隻蟲蟲有十條命，每次撞到牆壁、另一隻蟲或牠自己時就會失去一條命。敵人蟲蟲跟你有同樣的加成，因此要小心：如果他們變得太大，你不會有足夠的空間移動。

column1: The adventure progresses through 26 maps of increasing difficulty. The early levels are mostly open with a few walls, but later on, cramped spaces and teleporters make things more interesting.
column3: 冒險的旅程包括 26 張難度不斷增加的地圖。低等級的地圖大多是開放空間，也沒有什麼牆，但接下來，狹窄的空間和傳送點會讓事情愈來愈有趣。

column1: Play on your own against up to five enemy worms, or share your keyboard to play with a friend.
column3: 你可以對抗最多五隻敵人蟲蟲，或者也可以跟你的朋友共用鍵盤一起玩。

column1: A simple application to access, organize and share your photos on GNOME. It is meant to be a simple and elegant replacement for using a file manager to deal with photos. Seamless cloud integration is offered through GNOME Online Accounts.
column3: 簡單的應用程式，讓你可以在 GNOME 中存取、管理與分享你的相片。它希望能成為以檔案管理程式處理相片的優雅替代計劃。透過 GNOME 網上帳號提供無縫的雲端整合。

It is the distant future – the year 2000. Evil robots are trying to kill you. Avoid the robots or face certain death.
column3: 那是遙遠的未來─西元 2000 年。邪惡的機械人正嘗試殺了你。避開機械人或面對死亡。

column1: Fortunately, the robots are extremely stupid and will always move directly towards you. Trick them into colliding into each other, resulting in their destruction, or into the junk piles that result. You can defend yourself by moving the junk piles, or escape to safety with your handy teleportation device.
column3: 很幸運的，機械人相當笨，它們永遠只會直接向着你移動。誘導他們互相撞在一起，使他們撞毀，或是讓他們撞向垃圾堆也可以。你可以移動到垃圾堆以保護自己，或是使用你的手持傳送裝置安全的逃走。

column1: Your supply of safe teleports is limited, and once you run out, teleportation could land you right next to a robot, who will kill you. Survive for as long as possible!
column3: 你的安全傳送支援是有限制的，而且一旦你逃脫，傳送會將你送到機械人旁邊，可能會因此讓你送命。儘可能活久一點！

column1:
%s [OPTION...] COMMAND

Execute COMMAND while inhibiting some session functionality.

  -h, --help        Show this help
  --version         Show program version
  --app-id ID       The application id to use
                    when inhibiting (optional)
  --reason REASON   The reason for inhibiting (optional)
  --inhibit ARG     Things to inhibit, colon-separated list of:
                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount
  --inhibit-only    Do not launch COMMAND and wait forever instead

If no --inhibit option is specified, idle is assumed.
column3:
%s [OPTION...] COMMAND

抑制某些作業階段功能時執行 COMMAND 。

  -h, --help        顯示這個求助文件
  --version         顯示程式版本
  --app-id ID       抑制時要使用的
                    應用程式 id (選擇性)
  --reason REASON   抑制的原因 (選擇性)
  --inhibit ARG     要抑制的東西，以冒號分隔的清單：
                    logout, switch-user, suspend, idle, automount
  --inhibit-only    不要執行 COMMAND 而以等待來取代

如果沒有指定 --inhibit 選項，預設為 idle。

column1: File for default configuration for RandR

The XRandR plugin will look for a default configuration in the file specified by this key. This is similar to the ~/.config/monitors.xml that normally gets stored in users' home directories. If a user does not have such a file, or has one that does not match the user's setup of monitors, then the file specified by this key will be used instead.
column3: XRandR 外掛程式會在這個設定鍵指定的檔案中尋找預設的組態。這很類似通常儲存在使用者家目錄的 ~/.config/monitors.xml。如果使用者沒有這個檔案，或是雖然有卻不符含使用者的螢幕設定，就會以這個設定鍵指定的檔案來代替。

column1: 'clone' will display the same thing on all monitors, 'dock' will switch off the internal monitor, 'do-nothing' will use the default Xorg behaviour (extend the desktop in recent versions). The default, 'follow-lid', will choose between 'do-nothing' and 'dock' depending on whether the lid is (respectively) open or closed.
column3: 「clone」(複製) 會在所有螢幕顯示同樣東西，「dock」(停駐)會關閉內部螢幕，「do-nothing」(不做任何事) 會使用預設的 Xorg 行為 (在最近版本中為延伸桌面)。預設值中，「follow-lid」會根據上蓋開啟或關閉來選擇「do-nothing」和「dock」。

column1: The type of antialiasing to use when rendering fonts. Possible values are: \"none\" for no antialiasing, \"grayscale\" for standard grayscale antialiasing, and \"rgba\" for subpixel antialiasing (LCD screens only).

column1: The type of hinting to use when rendering fonts. Possible values are: \"none\" for no hinting, \"slight\" for basic, \"medium\" for moderate, and \"full\" for maximum hinting (may cause distortion of letter forms).
column3: 繪製字型時所用的 hinting 類型。可能的數值有：「none」為不使用 hinting，「slight」為基本式，「medium」為中等程度，而「full」是最大的 hinting（可能造成字體破碎）。

column1: The order of subpixel elements on an LCD screen; only used when antialiasing is set to \"rgba\". Possible values are: \"rgb\" for red on left (most common), \"bgr\" for blue on left, \"vrgb\" for red on top, \"vbgr\" for red on bottom.
column3: 在 LCD 螢幕上子像素元素的順序；只有在平滑化設為「rgba」時才能使用。可能的數值有：「rgb」為紅色在左(最常用)，「bgr」為藍色在左，「vrgb」為紅色在上，「vbgr」為紅色在下。

column1: List the contents of the locations.

gvfs-ls is similar to the traditional ls utility, but using gvfs
locations instead of local files: for example you can use something
like smb://server/resource/file.txt as location. File attributes can
be specified with their gvfs name, e.g. standard::icon.
column3:
gvfs-ls 運作方式就像傳統的 ls 公用程式，只是使用
 gvfs 位置代替 local 檔案：例如你可以使用像
smb://server/resource/file.txt 做為位置。檔案屬性
可以用它們的 gvfs 名稱指定，如：standard::icon。

column1: Hitori is a logic game similar to the popular game of Sudoku.
column3: Hitori 是一種類似數獨的邏輯遨遊戲。

column1: You play the game against the clock, aiming to eliminate all the duplicate numbers in each row and column in the fastest time. Multiple sizes of game board are supported, and you can place markers on cells to help work out the solution. If you get stuck, the game can give you a hint.
column3: 你要在時限內完成遊戲，目標是在最短時間內清除每一欄、每一列中重複的數字。遊戲盤支援多種尺寸，你可以在格子裏放上標記來協助找出解答。如果你卡關了，遊戲可以給你提示。

Iagno is a computer version of the game Reversi, a two-player strategy board game. The game is played with tiles that are dark on one side and light on the other.
column3: Iagno 是電腦版的 Reversi 遊戲，一種兩人策略桌游。這個遊戲是用兩種棋子，一黑一白來玩。

column1: The object of Iagno is to flip as many of your opponent's tiles to your color as possible while preventing your opponent from flipping your tiles to his color. This is done by trapping your opponent's tiles between two tiles of your own color.
column3: Iagno 的目的是盡可能把你的對手的棋翻成你的顏色，同時避免你的對手將你的棋翻成他的顏色。要達成這個目標可以讓對手的棋被你自己的顏色夾住即可困住他。

column1: Lights Off is a collection of light switch puzzles. Clicking on a light toggles it either on or off, but also toggles all the surrounding lights, too. Your objective is simple: turn off all the lights!
column3: 關燈遊戲是切換燈號遊戲的集合。點選燈會讓它開啟或關閉，但也同時會切換它周圍的燈號。你的目的很簡單：關掉所有的燈！

column1: Players who delight in turning off lights will enjoy the huge number of levels.

column1: Nautilus, also known as Files, is the default file manager of the GNOME desktop. It provides a simple and integrated way of managing your files and browsing your file system.
column3: Nautilus，亦稱為 Files (檔案)，是 GNOME 桌面的預設檔案管理程式。它提供了簡易與整合的方法讓你管理與瀏覽檔案系統。

column1: Nautilus supports all the basic functions of a file manager and more. It can search and manage your files and folders, both locally and on a network, read and write data to and from removable media, run scripts, and launch applications. It has three views: Icon Grid, Icon List, and Tree List. Its functions can be extended with plugins and scripts.
column3: Nautilus 支援檔案管理的所有基礎功能，甚至更多。它可以搜尋與管理你的檔案與資料夾，無論是本地端或是網絡；讀寫可移除媒體的資料、執行命令稿與應用程式。它有三種檢視：圖示格線、圖示清單和樹狀清單。它的功能可以透過外掛程式與命令稿擴充。
folder;manager;explore;disk;filesystem;資料夾;管理程式;磁碟;檔案系統;

column1: If set to \"after-current-tab\", then new tabs are inserted after the current tab. If set to \"end\", then new tabs are appended to the end of the tab list.
column3: 如果設為「after_current_tab」，則新的分頁會插入到目前分頁之後。如果設為「end」，則新的分頁會加到分頁清單的最後端。

column1: Always use the location entry, instead of the pathbar
column3: 總是使用需要輸入的位置列，而非路徑列

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus browser windows will always use a textual input entry for the location toolbar, instead of the pathbar.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，Nautilus 瀏覽器視窗會使用輸入文字項目的位置工具列，而非路徑列。

column1: Whether to ask for confirmation when deleting files, or emptying Trash
column3: 刪除檔案或清空回收筒時是否需要確認

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will ask for confirmation when you attempt to delete files, or empty the Trash.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，Nautilus 會在你嘗試刪除檔案或清空回收筒時先進行確認。
是否啟用立即刪除功能

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will have a feature allowing you to delete a file immediately and in-place, instead of moving it to the trash. This feature can be dangerous, so use caution.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，Nautilus 會提供另一種功能，讓你即時刪除檔案，而不是將檔案丟進回收筒。本功能是比較危險，所以請小心使用。

column1: When to show number of items in a folder
column3: 何時會在資料夾中顯示有多少個項目

column1: Speed tradeoff for when to show the number of items in a folder. If set to \"always\" then always show item counts, even if the folder is on a remote server. If set to \"local-only\" then only show counts for local file systems. If set to \"never\" then never bother to compute item counts.
column3: 有關顯示目錄中的檔案數目在速度方面的權衡。如果設定為“always”，即使是遠端目錄仍然會顯示數目。如果設定為“local-only”則只會在本地檔案系統的目錄顯示數目。如果設定為“never”則不會計算數目。

column1: Type of click used to launch/open files
column3: 啟動/開啟檔案的按滑鼠按鈕方式

column1: Possible values are \"single\" to launch files on a single click, or \"double\" to launch them on a double click.
column3: 如何啟動檔案。可接受的值為：\n“single”：按一下滑鼠按鈕\n“double”：連按兩下滑鼠按鈕

column1: What to do with executable text files when activated
column3: 當按下可執行的文字檔時，會以哪種方式處理

column1: What to do with executable text files when they are activated (single or double clicked). Possible values are \"launch\" to launch them as programs, \"ask\" to ask what to do via a dialog, and \"display\" to display them as text files.
column3:
當按下（按一下或連按兩下）可執行的文字檔時，會以哪一種方式處理。可接受的值為：
“launch”會將它們當作程式來執行，
“ask”會顯示對話盒詢問使用者，
“display”會以文字檔方式顯示內容。

column1: Show the package installer for unknown mime types
column3: 是否對不明的 mime 類型顯示套件安裝程式

column1: Whether to show the user a package installer dialog in case an unknown mime type is opened, in order to search for an application to handle it.
column3: 是否在開啟不明的 mime 類型時顯示套件安裝程式對話盒，以便搜尋能處理它的應用程式。

column1: Use extra mouse button events in Nautilus' browser window
column3: 是否在 Nautilus 瀏覽器視窗中使用額外的滑鼠按鈕事件

column1: For users with mice that have \"Forward\" and \"Back\" buttons, this key will determine if any action is taken inside of Nautilus when either is pressed.
column3: 用於使用者的滑鼠有「往前」和「往後」按鈕時，這個設定鍵會決定當 Nautilus 被按下時所進行的行動。

column1: Mouse button to activate the \"Forward\" command in browser window
column3: 用來觸發瀏覽器視窗中「下一頁」指令的滑鼠按鈕

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for \"Forward\" and \"Back\", this key will set which button activates the \"Forward\" command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.
column3: 用於使用者的滑鼠有「往前」和「往後」按鈕時，這個設定鍵會決定哪個按鈕會觸發瀏覽器視窗中的「下一頁」指令。可能的數值範圍在 6 到 14 之間。

column1: Mouse button to activate the \"Back\" command in browser window
column3: 用來觸發瀏覽器視窗中「上一頁」指令的滑鼠按鈕

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for \"Forward\" and \"Back\", this key will set which button activates the \"Back\" command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.
column3: 用於使用者的滑鼠有「往前」和「往後」按鈕時，這個設定鍵會決定哪個按鈕會觸發瀏覽器視窗中的「上一頁」指令。可能的數值範圍在 6 到 14 之間。

column1: When to show thumbnails of files
column3: 何時會顯示檔案的縮圖

column1: Speed tradeoff for when to show a file as a thumbnail. If set to \"always\" then always thumbnail, even if the folder is on a remote server. If set to \"local-only\" then only show thumbnails for local file systems. If set to \"never\" then never bother to thumbnail files, just use a generic icon. Despite what the name may suggest, this applies to any previewable file type.
column3: 有關顯示檔案時是否以縮圖來代替在速度方面的權衡。如果設定為“always”，即使是遠端伺服器上的資料夾仍然會顯示縮圖。如果設定為“local-only”則只會顯示本地檔案系統的縮圖。如果設定為“never”則不會顯示縮圖，只會用一般的圖示代替。不論可能建議的名稱為何，這個選項會套用到任何可預覽的檔案類型。
所產生的縮圖的圖片大小上限

column1: Images over this size (in bytes) won't be thumbnailed. The purpose of this setting is to avoid thumbnailing large images that may take a long time to load or use lots of memory.
column3: 不會為超過指定大小（以位元組計算）的圖片產生縮圖。這個設定的目的是避免為太大的圖片產生縮圖，消耗過多的時間或記憶體。
在視窗中先顯示資料夾

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus shows folders prior to showing files in the icon and list views.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，Nautilus 會在圖示顯示模式及清單顯示模式中先顯示目錄，然後才顯示檔案。

column1: The default sort-order for items in the icon view. Possible values are \"name\", \"size\", \"type\" and \"mtime\".
column3: 在圖示顯示模式中，各項目的預設排列方式。可接受的值為“name”、“size”、“type”和“mtime”。

column1: Reverse sort order in new windows
column3: 在新的視窗中以相反次序排列

column1: If true, files in new windows will be sorted in reverse order. ie, if sorted by name, then instead of sorting the files from \"a\" to \"z\", they will be sorted from \"z\" to \"a\"; if sorted by size, instead of being incrementally they will be sorted decrementally.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，在新的視窗中檔案會以相反次序排列。譬如說，如果是以檔案名稱來排列，本來從“a”至“z”排列的檔案會改為從“z”至“a”排列；如果是以檔案大小來排列，本來是遞增排列的，現在會變成遞減。
預設的資料夾顯示模式

column1: When a folder is visited this viewer is used unless you have selected another view for that particular folder. Possible values are \"list-view\", and \"icon-view\".
column3: 當開啟資料夾時，除非特地為該資料夾選取了顯示模式，否則預設會使用這個顯示模式。可接受的值為「list-view」及「icon-view」。

column1: This key is deprecated and ignored. The \"show-hidden\" key from \"org.gtk.Settings.FileChooser\" is now used instead.
column3: 這個設定鍵已廢棄並忽略。現在使用「org.gtk.Settings.FileChooser」的「show-hidden」設定鍵。
大量重新命名公用程式

column1: If set, Nautilus will append URIs of selected files and treat the result as a command line for bulk renaming. Bulk rename applications can register themselves in this key by setting the key to a space-separated string of their executable name and any command line options. If the executable name is not set to a full path, it will be searched for in the search path.
column3: 如果設定，Nautilus 會加入選取檔案的 URI 並將結果當成大量重新命名的指令。大量重新命名程式可以將它們自身註冊於這個設定鍵，只要把設定鍵設為以空白分隔的字串，包含它們的執行名稱與任何命令列選項。如果執行名稱沒有設為完整路徑，將會在搜尋路徑中自動搜尋。

column1: List of possible captions on icons
column3: 圖示下方可以出現的標題

column1: A list of captions below an icon in the icon view and the desktop. The actual number of captions shown depends on the zoom level. Some possible values are: \"size\", \"type\", \"date_modified\", \"owner\", \"group\", \"permissions\", and \"mime_type\".
column3: 這是在圖示顯示模式中，或者在桌面中，圖示下方附帶的一系列標題文字。實際會顯示的標題數目取決於縮放倍率。可接受的值為：「size」、「type」、「date_modified」、「owner」、「group」、「permissions」及「mime_type」。

column1: Default zoom level used by the icon view.
column3: 圖示顯示模式的預設縮放倍率。

column1: The default size of an icon for a thumbnail in the icon view.
column3: 圖示顯示模式中預設顯示的圖示大小。

column1: A string specifying how parts of overlong file names should be replaced by ellipses, depending on the zoom level. Each of the list entries is of the form \"Zoom Level:Integer\". For each specified zoom level, if the given integer is larger than 0, the file name will not exceed the given number of lines. If the integer is 0 or smaller, no limit is imposed on the specified zoom level. A default entry of the form \"Integer\" without any specified zoom level is also allowed. It defines the maximum number of lines for all other zoom levels. Examples: 0 - always display overlong file names; 3 - shorten file names if they exceed three lines; smallest:5,smaller:4,0 - shorten file names if they exceed five lines for zoom level \"smallest\". Shorten file names if they exceed four lines for zoom level \"smaller\". Do not shorten file names for other zoom levels. Available zoom levels: smallest (33%), smaller (50%), small (66%), standard (100%), large (150%), larger (200%), largest (400%)
column3: 根據據縮放等級，決定過長的檔案名稱的一部分要以省略符號替換的字串值。每個清單項目的格式為 \"縮放等級:整數值\"。針對每個指定的縮放等級，如果所給的整數值大於 0，則檔案名稱的長度將不會超過該整數值的列數。如果該整數值小於或等於 0，表示對指定的縮放等級不予限制長度。若以 \"整數值\" 的格式不指定縮放等級也可以接受為項目的預設值，它將會定義所有未指定的縮放等級的最大列數。例如： 0 - 永遠完整顥示過長的檔案名稱：3 - 如果超過 3 行則截短檔案名稱：smallest:5,smaller:4,0 - 在縮放等級 \"smallest\" 中超過 5 行就截短檔案名稱；在縮放等級 \"smaller\" 中超過 4 行就截短檔案名稱；其他的縮放等級則不會截短檔案名稱。可用的縮放等級有：smallest (33%)、 smaller (50%)、 small (66%)、 standard (100%)、 large (150%)、 larger (200%)、 largest (400%)

column1: Default zoom level used by the list view.
column3: 清單顯示模式的預設縮放倍率。

column1: Default list of columns visible in the list view
column3: 清單顯示模式中預設顯示的欄位

column1: Default list of columns visible in the list view.
column3: 清單顯示模式中預設顯示的欄位。

column1: Default column order in the list view
column3: 清單顯示模式中預設的欄位次序

column1: Default column order in the list view.
column3: 清單顯示模式中預設的欄位次序。

column1: Whether a tree should be used for list view navigation instead of a flat list
column3: 樹狀檢視是否用於清單檢視導覽以取代普通清單

column1: The font description used for the icons on the desktop.
column3: 桌面圖示所使用的字型描述。
在桌面中顯示「個人資料夾」圖示

column1: If this is set to true, an icon linking to the home folder will be put on the desktop.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，則桌面上會有一個圖示連結至「個人資料夾」。
在桌面上顯示「回收筒」圖示

column1: If this is set to true, an icon linking to the trash will be put on the desktop.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，則桌面上會有一個圖示連結至回收筒。

column1: Show mounted volumes on the desktop
column3: 在桌面上顯示已掛載的儲存區

column1: If this is set to true, icons linking to mounted volumes will be put on the desktop.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，則桌面上會出現連結到已掛載的儲存區的圖示。

column1: Network Servers icon visible on the desktop
column3: 在桌面中顯示網絡伺服器圖示

column1: If this is set to true, an icon linking to the Network Servers view will be put on the desktop.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，則桌面上會有一個圖示連結至顯示網絡伺服器。
桌面中「個人資料夾」圖示的名稱

column1: This name can be set if you want a custom name for the home icon on the desktop.
column3: 如果你想為桌面上的「個人資料夾」圖示自選名稱，可以在這裏設定。
桌面中「回收筒」圖示的名稱

column1: This name can be set if you want a custom name for the trash icon on the desktop.
column3: 如果你想為桌面上的「回收筒」圖示自選名稱，可以在這裏設定。

column1: This name can be set if you want a custom name for the network servers icon on the desktop.
column3: 如果你想為桌面上的「網絡伺服器」圖示自選名稱，可以在這裏設定。

column1: An integer specifying how parts of overlong file names should be replaced by ellipses on the desktop. If the number is larger than 0, the file name will not exceed the given number of lines. If the number is 0 or smaller, no limit is imposed on the number of displayed lines.
column3: 決定桌面上過長的檔案名稱的一部分要以省略符號替換的字串值。如果所給的整數值大於 0，則檔案名稱的長度將不會超過該整數值的列數。如果該整數值小於或等於 0，表示對指定的縮放等級不予限制長度。

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will use a fade effect to change the desktop background.
column3: 如設定為「true」，Nautilus 會在改變桌面背景時使用淡化效果。

column1: The geometry string for a navigation window.
column3: 導覽視窗的位置大小字串。

column1: A string containing the saved geometry and coordinates string for navigation windows.
column3: 包含儲存導覽視窗大小和坐標的字串。

column1: Whether the navigation window should be maximized.
column3: 導覽視窗是否該被最大化。

column1: Whether the navigation window should be maximized by default.
column3: 導覽視窗是否預設最大化。

column1: The default width of the side pane in new windows.
column3: 側面窗格在新的視窗中的預設闊度。

column1: Show location bar in new windows
column3: 在新的視窗中顯示位置列

column1: If set to true, newly opened windows will have the location bar visible.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，新的視窗會顯示位置列。

column1: Show side pane in new windows
column3: 在新的視窗中顯示側面窗格

column1: If set to true, newly opened windows will have the side pane visible.
column3: 如設定為‘true’，新開啟的視窗會顯示側面窗格。
糟糕！有些地方出問題了。

column1: Unable to create a required folder. Please create the following folder, or set permissions such that it can be created:\n%s
column3: 無法建立需要的資料夾。請自行建立以下資料夾，或是設定正確的權限以便建立這些資料夾：\n%s

column1: Unable to create required folders. Please create the following folders, or set permissions such that they can be created:\n%s
column3: 無法建立需要的資料夾。請自行建立以下資料夾，或是設定正確的權限以便建立這些資料夾：\n%s

column1: Nautilus 3.0 deprecated this directory and tried migrating this configuration to ~/.config/nautilus
column3: Nautilus 3.0 已廢棄這個目錄並且嘗試將這個組態轉移到 ~/.config/nautilus

column1: There was an error displaying help: \n%s
column3: 顯示說明文件時發生錯誤：\n%s

column1: --check cannot be used with other options.
column3: --check 不可配合其他選項使用。
--quit 不能與 URIs 一起使用。

column1: --geometry cannot be used with more than one URI.
column3: --geometry 不適用於多於一個 URI。

column1: --select must be used with at least an URI.
column3: --select 必須它至少有一個 URI。

column1: Perform a quick set of self-check tests.
column3: 執行快速自動檢查測試。

column1: Show the version of the program.
Create the initial window with the given geometry.
column3: 以指定尺寸顯示初始視窗。

column1: Always open a new window for browsing specified URIs
column3: 瀏覽指定 URI 時永遠開啟新的視窗

column1: Only create windows for explicitly specified URIs.
column3: 只有特別指定 URI 時才會開啟新的視窗。

column1: Never manage the desktop (ignore the GSettings preference).
column3: 不管理桌面 (會忽略 GSettings 偏好設定)。

column1: Always manage the desktop (ignore the GSettings preference).
column3: 永遠管理桌面 (會忽略 GSettings 偏好設定)。

column1: Select specified URI in parent folder.
column3: 請選擇上層資料夾的指定 URI。

column1: \n\nBrowse the file system with the file manager
column3: \n\n使用檔案總管瀏覽檔案系統

column1: Oops! There was a problem running this software.
column3: 噢！執行這個軟件時發生問題。

column1: “%s” contains software intended to be automatically started. Would you like to run it?
column3: “%s” 包含了要求自動執行的軟件。是否要執行它？

column1: If you don't trust this location or aren't sure, press Cancel.
column3: 如果你不信任這個位置或不確定，請按「取消」。

column1: Display icons in the opposite order
Keep icons lined up on a grid
Leave icons wherever they are dropped
column3: 拖放圖示後不自動編排圖示的位置

column1: Keep icons sorted by name in rows
Keep icons sorted by size in rows
Keep icons sorted by type in rows
Keep icons sorted by modification date in rows
Keep icons sorted by access date in rows
Keep icons sorted by trash time in rows
column3: 以回收筒時刻排列圖示

column1: Keep icons sorted by search relevance in rows
Print but do not open the URI
This file server type is not recognized.
column3: 這個檔案伺服器的類型無法辨識。

column1: This doesn't look like an address.
Show a window that lets you set your desktop background's pattern or color
column3: 顯示一個可設定桌面背景圖樣或顏色的視窗

column1: Delete all items in the Trash
Reposition icons to better fit in the window and avoid overlapping
column3: 重新排列圖示以符合視窗及避免重疊
將選取的圖示設為可改變大小

column1: Restore each selected icon to its original size
column3: 還原所有選取圖示的尺寸

column1: You do not have the permissions necessary to view the contents of “%s”.
column3: 你沒有檢視“%s”的內容所需的權限。

column1: “%s” could not be found. Perhaps it has recently been deleted.
column3: 找不到“%s”。可能它剛剛已被刪除。

column1: Sorry, could not display all the contents of “%s”: %s
column3: 抱歉，無法顯示“%s”的所有內容：%s

column1: This location could not be displayed.
You do not have the permissions necessary to change the group of “%s”.
column3: 你沒有更改“%s”羣組所需的權限。

column1: Sorry, could not change the group of “%s”: %s
column3: 抱歉，無法更改“%s”的所屬羣組：%s

column1: The group could not be changed.
Sorry, could not change the owner of “%s”: %s
column3: 抱歉，無法更改“%s”的擁有者：%s

column1: The owner could not be changed.
Sorry, could not change the permissions of “%s”: %s
The permissions could not be changed.
The name “%s” is already used in this location. Please use a different name.
column3: 這個位置內已經有名為“%s”的項目。請使用不同的名稱。

column1: There is no “%s” in this location. Perhaps it was just moved or deleted?
column3: 這個位置內沒有“%s”。也許它剛剛被移動或刪除了？

column1: You do not have the permissions necessary to rename “%s”.
column3: 你沒有重新命名“%s”所需的權限。

column1: The name “%s” is not valid because it contains the character “/”. Please use a different name.
column3: 名稱“%s”無效，因為它含有字符“/”。請使用不同的名稱。

column1: The name “%s” is not valid. Please use a different name.
column3: 名稱“%s”無效。請使用不同的名稱。

column1: The name “%s” is too long. Please use a different name.
column3: 名稱“%s”太長。請使用不同的名稱。
抱歉，無法將“%s”重新命名為“%s”：%s

column1: Quadrapassel is a derivative of a classic Russian falling-block game. Reposition and rotate the blocks as they fall, and attempt to fit them together. When you form a complete horizontal row of blocks, the row will disappear and you score points. The game is over when the blocks get stacked too high. As your score gets higher, you level up and the blocks fall faster.
column3: Quadrapassel 是傳統的俄羅斯方塊遊戲。在方塊落下時重新定位並將它們旋轉，並嘗試讓它們組合在一起。當你完成水平整列的方塊時，那一列就會消失，而你也會獲得分數。這個遊戲會在方塊堆積太高時結束。當你的分數愈高，你的等級會提高，而方塊也會掉得愈快。

column1: If you're looking for a challenge, Quadrapassel allows you to increase the initial speed of the blocks, or begin the game with partial blocks on some of the rows. Or, instead of allowing the blocks to fall randomly, it can select blocks that will be hard for you to place.
column3: 如果你尋求挑戰，Quadrapassel 能讓你增加方塊初始落下的速度，或是一開始遊戲時就有部分方塊在畫面上。或者，不使用隨機的方式選擇方塊，而是選擇比較難以放置的方塊給你。
將不同形狀而且不斷跌下的方塊拼合在一起

column1: Remove as many squares as possible from the board. Click on a group of squares of the same color to make them all disappear in one fell swoop, causing other squares to fall into place. It is not possible to remove a single square at a time. You get far more points for clearing a larger group of squares, and also for clearing the entire board.
column3: 儘可能將遊戲盤上的方塊移除。點選一羣同顏色的方塊能讓它們一次消失，但是會讓其他的方塊變色。如果一次清除比較大羣的方塊，你所獲得的分數也會大大提升，清除整個遊戲盤時也會有大量加分。

column1: The  scheduler  is  the kernel component that decides which runnable application will be executed by the CPU next.  Each application has an associated scheduling  policy and priority.\n\nThis option allows you to make Tracker take a back seat and not eat up too much CPU time if you have other applications more deserving of it.

column1: The  scheduler  is  the kernel component that decides which runnable application will be executed by the CPU next. column1: Enable remote access to the desktop
column3: 啟用遠端對桌面的存取

column1: If true, allows remote access to the desktop via the RFB protocol. Users on remote machines may then connect to the desktop using a VNC viewer.
column3: 如設定為 true，允許遠端電腦以 RFB 協定使用桌面。遠端電腦的使用者就可以用 VNC viewer 連接到桌面。

column1: Prompt the user before completing a connection
column3: 在完成連接前提示使用者

column1: If true, remote users accessing the desktop are not allowed access until the user on the host machine approves the connection. Recommended especially when access is not password protected.
column3: 如設定為 true，除非是在主機的用戶允許，否則遠端使用者不被允許使用桌面。建議使用，特別是沒有密碼保護的情形下。

column1: Only allow remote users to view the desktop
column3: 只允許遠端使用者去觀看桌面

column1: If true, remote users accessing the desktop are only allowed to view the desktop. Remote users will not be able to use the mouse or keyboard.
column3: 如設定為 true，遠端使用者僅被允許觀看桌面。他們將無法使用滑鼠或鍵盤。

column1: If not set, the server will listen on all network interfaces.\n\nSet this if you want to accept connections only from some specific network interface. For example, eth0, wifi0, lo and so on.
column3: 如果不設定，伺服器就會聽取所有的網絡介面。\n\n如果你只想接受來自特定網絡介面的連線就設定它。例如：eth0、wifi0、lo 等等。

column1: If true, the server will listen on another port, instead of the default (5900). The port must be specified in the 'alternative-port' key.
column3: 如設定為 true，該伺服器會監聽其他連接埠，而非預設值 (5900)。此連接埠必須在「alternative-port」設定鍵中指定。

column1: The port which the server will listen to if the 'use-alternative-port' key is set to true. Valid values are in the range of 5000 to 50000.
column3: 如「use-alternative-port」鍵值設為 true 時，伺服器要監聽的連接埠。可用的數值範圍為 5000 到 50000。

column1: If true, remote users accessing the desktop are required to support encryption. It is highly recommended that you use a client which supports encryption unless the intervening network is trusted.
column3: 如設定為 true，要存取桌面的遠端使用者必須支援加密。強烈建議使用支援加密的客戶端，除非兩者間的網絡是可信賴的。

column1: Lists the authentication methods with which remote users may access the desktop.\n\nThere are two possible authentication methods; \"vnc\" causes the remote user to be prompted for a password (the password is specified by the vnc-password key) before connecting and \"none\" which allows any remote user to connect.
column3: 列出遠端使用者可以使用的核對方式。\n\n有兩種可能的核對方式：一是「vnc」，即在連接前提示遠端使用者輸入密碼 (此密碼是由 vnc-password 設定鍵決定)，或者是「none」，即允許任何遠端使用者連接。

column1: The password which the remote user will be prompted for if the \"vnc\" authentication method is used. The password specified by the key is base64 encoded.\n\nThe special value of 'keyring' (which is not valid base64) means that the password is stored in the GNOME keyring.
column3: 如果使用「vnc」核對方法的話，遠端使用者需要輸入這個密碼。此密碼是用 base64 編碼的。\n\n若看到特殊的數值「keyring」(不是有效的 base64) 表示密碼是儲存在 GNOME 密碼匙圈裏。

column1: E-mail address to which the remote desktop URL should be sent
column3: 遠端桌面的 URL 應該寄送至這個電郵地址

column1: This key specifies the e-mail address to which the remote desktop URL should be sent if the user clicks on the URL in the Desktop Sharing preferences dialog.
column3: 這個設定鍵所指定的電子郵件位址是當使用者按下桌面分享偏好設定對話方塊中的 URL，遠端桌面網址應寄送的位址。

column1: Lock the screen when last user disconnect
column3: 當最後的使用者斷線時鎖定畫面

column1: If true, the screen will be locked after the last remote client disconnects.
column3: 如設定為 true，畫面會在最後的遠端客戶端斷線後鎖定。

column1: When the status icon should be shown

This key controls the behavior of the status icon. There are three options: \"always\" - the icon will always be present; \"client\" - the icon will only be present when someone is connected (this is the default behavior); \"never\" - the icon will not be present.
column3: 這個設定鍵控制了狀態圖示的行為。一共有三種選項：「always」(總是)─ 總是顯示圖示；「client」(客戶端) ─ 只在有人連線時才顯示圖示 (這是預設的行為)；「never」(永不) ─ 永遠不顯示圖示。

column1: Whether to disable the desktop background when a user is connected
column3: 當有使用者連線時是否停用桌面背景

column1: When true, disable the desktop background and replace it with a single block of color when a user successfully connects.
column3: 當 true 時，有使用者成功連線時停用桌面背景並以單一顏色區塊取代它。

column1: Whether a UPnP router should be used to forward and open ports
column3: 是否要使用 UPnP 在路由器中轉址與開啟連接埠

column1: If true, request that a UPnP-capable router should forward and open the port used by Vino.
column3: 如果設定為 true，要求支援 UPnP 的路由器應該轉址並開啟 Vino 使用的連接埠。

column1: Whether we should disable the XDamage extension of X.org
column3: 我們是否要停用 X.org 的 XDamage 延伸功能

column1: If true, do not use the XDamage extension of X.org. This extension does not work properly on some video drivers when using 3D effects. Disabling it will make Vino work in these environments, with slower rendering as a side effect.
column3: 如果設為 true，我們將不會使用 X.org 的 XDamage 延伸功能。這項延伸功能在部分視像驅動程式下使用 3D 效果時無法正常運作。將它停用的副作用為 Vino 在這些環境下的繪製速度會變得較慢。

column1: If true, show a notification when a user connects to the system.
column3: 如果設為 true，當使用者連線到系統時顯示通知。
